  "sentences": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "start": 5.962,
      "end": 15.496,
      "text": "Mysteries of vernacular: Sarcophagus, a stone coffin typically adorned with decorative carvings or inscriptions.",
      "translation": "词源揭秘：“Sarcophagus”，一座石质棺材，通常带有雕刻和铭文做装饰。"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "start": 15.546,
      "end": 24.667,
      "text": "The history of the word sarcophagus is so skin-crawlingly grotesque, it seems to come right out of a low-budget horror film.",
      "translation": "“Sarcophagus”一词的历史是如此令人毛骨悚然，以至于它好像是从低成本恐怖电影中出来的一样。"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "start": 24.717,
      "end": 40.0,
      "text": "Rather than having a B-movie origin, however, its roots can be traced back to the early Roman Empire where the Greek word sarkophagus was used to describe the limestone that a coffin was made of, not the coffin itself.",
      "translation": "不过它并不是从B级电影中出来的，它的源头可以追溯到罗马帝国早起。当时希腊语单词“sarkophagus”用来描述制作棺材的石灰岩，不是棺材本身。"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "start": 40.05,
      "end": 50.048,
      "text": "According to the Roman scholar Pliny the Elder, citizens of the Empire believed that limestone from a quarry near Troy would dissolve flesh.",
      "translation": "据罗马学者老普林尼说，帝国的公民相信特洛伊附近采石场出产的石灰岩能分解肉体。"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "start": 50.098,
      "end": 55.087,
      "text": "For this reason, it was quite desireable in the construction of coffins.",
      "translation": "正因如此，该材质很适合用来制作棺材。"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "start": 55.137,
      "end": 72.792,
      "text": "Though it's unclear if the belief was widespread or even accurately reported by Pliny, what is certain is that sarkophagus came from the Greek words sark, meaning flesh, and phagein, a verb meaning to eat.",
      "translation": "说法是否普遍，以及普林尼的记载是否准确并不清楚，但可以确定的是，“sarkophagus”来自希腊语“sark”，意思是肉体，和“phagein”，动词，意思是吃。"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "start": 72.842,
      "end": 80.95,
      "text": "From flesh-eating stone to stone coffin, it's a fitting etymology for the final resting place of the deceased.",
      "translation": "从吃肉的岩石到石质棺材，这个语源倒是与逝者的最后栖息地相符。"
    }
  ],
